Incidental demonstration of pericardial fistula during hepatobiliary scintigraphy.
 Biliary vomiting developed 16 mo after resection of adenocarcinoma of the esophagus in a patient with a complex postoperative course.
 A biliary scan revealed an outline of the pericardium, suggesting a fistula.
 The potential role of radionuclide imaging in this rare and potentially fatal complication is discussed.
